# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules
#
# Strip trailing slashes — 301-redirect every path ending in "/" to the
# canonical no-trailing-slash form so Google sees a single authoritative URL.
# This pairs with the canonical normalisation in SEOHead.astro and the
# sitemap serializer in astro.config.mjs.
#
# Pattern  /*/  matches /blog/, /about/, /blog/some-post/, etc.
# :splat   captures everything before the final "/" and reuses it as the target.
# The root path "/" is NOT matched — it has no leading segment before the slash.
#
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

/*/  /:splat  301
